cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper introduces an information-theoretic metric, the delivery time per bit (DTB), and establishes lower and upper bounds on it. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a Fog radio access network (F-RAN) architecture and analyzes the performance of cloud and cache aided heterogeneous networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers a network architecture and analyzes its performance in terms of reliability, spectral efficiency, and latency. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses a distributed network architecture with centralized cloud processing and wireless edge caching. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers the delivery of requested content to mobile users in a wireless network.
